1
00:00:02,236 --> 00:00:05,840
The mysterious realtor prince Kenji Rusudo

2
00:00:06,107 --> 00:00:09,243
has crushed Machi Sangenya.

3
00:00:09,944 --> 00:00:11,512
Who are you going to battle with?

4
00:00:12,046 --> 00:00:13,180
With the person I love.

5
00:00:13,447 --> 00:00:16,784
The shock of her defeat
left everyone speechless.

6
00:00:17,118 --> 00:00:18,252
I lost.

7
00:00:19,086 --> 00:00:22,323
Who exactly is Kenji Rusudo?

8
00:00:22,923 --> 00:00:25,826
She was homeless once.

9
00:00:26,327 --> 00:00:28,763
Does the genius realtor Machi Sangenya

10
00:00:29,330 --> 00:00:31,632
have a counterattack measure?

11
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:37,071
A new chapter in the battle
is about to begin.

12
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:45,312
I can only assume that our data
is being leaked.

13
00:00:48,482 --> 00:00:49,717
I have nothing to do with it.

14
00:00:49,784 --> 00:00:52,386
I'm not doubting you,

15
00:00:52,453 --> 00:00:56,323
but that Rusudo guy's obsession
with Sangenya is not normal.

16
00:00:57,925 --> 00:00:59,260
There's the ex-boyfriend theory too.

17
00:01:00,528 --> 00:01:02,029
I don't think that's a possibility.

18
00:01:02,096 --> 00:01:03,864
What are you upset about, Niwano?

19
00:01:03,931 --> 00:01:07,134
As far as Chief Sangenya is concerned,
there's no way he's her ex-boyfriend!

20
00:01:07,535 --> 00:01:11,806
You think so? She's very beautiful.
She could have an ex-boyfriend.

21
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:15,543
Are you maybe jealous of Rusudo?

22
00:01:15,609 --> 00:01:16,477
Oh!

23
00:01:16,544 --> 00:01:19,613
Oh, Niwano, are you jealous?

24
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:20,781
Of course not!

25
00:01:20,848 --> 00:01:23,317
It's even more suspicious
when you get all worked up.

26
00:01:23,384 --> 00:01:24,985
Don't get all worked up over it.

27
00:01:25,453 --> 00:01:27,087
Good work.

28
00:01:27,455 --> 00:01:29,056
Good work.

29
00:01:29,457 --> 00:01:32,660
She can go home under this circumstance?

30
00:01:35,463 --> 00:01:37,798
-We have a problem!
-What is it?

31
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:42,269
Welcome back.

32
00:01:59,653 --> 00:02:03,324
JINKEUDORUSU
UDOSURUNJIKE

33
00:02:03,390 --> 00:02:04,959
Ujindokesuru?

34
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:07,628
Is that a Mongolian name?

35
00:02:08,462 --> 00:02:10,397
Chief Sangenya, please get it together.

36
00:02:10,831 --> 00:02:12,233
-Manager!
-Yes.

37
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:15,503
I will be taking paid vacation
for a while.

38
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:17,304
What?

39
00:02:26,213 --> 00:02:29,250
You've been late 20 times already.
Do you know what this means?

40
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:31,685
I don't. I've been late that many times?

41
00:02:32,052 --> 00:02:33,921
We promised that one unexcused absence

42
00:02:33,988 --> 00:02:36,290
or three unexcused tardiness
will get you fired, right?

43
00:02:36,357 --> 00:02:37,691
You don't have to come anymore.

44
00:02:37,892 --> 00:02:42,730
Oh, how cold blooded is that!
I'm a poor single mother!

45
00:02:42,796 --> 00:02:47,968
That's why I gave you a pass 20 times.
That's it though. This is for today.

46
00:02:48,035 --> 00:02:50,771
You've got to be kidding me!

47
00:02:51,005 --> 00:02:55,175
I need to work here
to put my child in day care.

48
00:02:55,242 --> 00:02:57,545
And yet, you are going to fire me?

49
00:02:58,112 --> 00:03:01,882
What are you shouting for?
We could hear you outside.

50
00:03:01,949 --> 00:03:03,250
I got laid off.

51
00:03:03,484 --> 00:03:06,754
A firing of an employee
by an unreasonable owner

52
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:07,821
shouldn't be ignored!

53
00:03:07,888 --> 00:03:10,057
Stand up, single mother!

54
00:03:10,124 --> 00:03:11,458
Sure, sure. Beer please.

55
00:03:11,725 --> 00:03:13,127
Do it yourself!

56
00:03:13,694 --> 00:03:14,929
She's taking it out on me.

57
00:03:17,031 --> 00:03:19,099
-Is Sangenya here?
-What?

58
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:20,768
She's not here, huh.

59
00:03:21,035 --> 00:03:23,003
Chief Sangenya didn't go home?

60
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:24,939
When I got home,

61
00:03:25,005 --> 00:03:27,374
there was a note that said,
"I'll be gone for a while,

62
00:03:27,441 --> 00:03:30,311
I'll be back for sure.
Please do not worry."

63
00:03:30,377 --> 00:03:33,080
"I'll be back for sure, don't worry,"
is what people say

64
00:03:33,147 --> 00:03:34,615
then they have no intention of returning.

65
00:03:35,082 --> 00:03:36,584
What are you saying, Kokoro!

66
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:39,887
There were times she didn't return home
to sell properties,

67
00:03:40,187 --> 00:03:43,290
but this time, she's not home
while she's on a paid vacation!

68
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:47,194
Maybe she just went
to a hot spring for fun?

69
00:03:47,261 --> 00:03:49,196
If that's the case, I'm fine.

70
00:03:49,263 --> 00:03:51,532
As a manager and her boss,

71
00:03:51,599 --> 00:03:55,769
I'm glad that Sangenya is taking some
time off work, since she works too much

72
00:03:55,836 --> 00:03:58,105
and I was afraid headquarters
would find out soon enough.

73
00:03:58,539 --> 00:04:00,574
But as her husband,

74
00:04:00,641 --> 00:04:04,845
I'm sad my wife has gone off somewhere
while on paid vacation.

75
00:04:05,112 --> 00:04:09,249
I wonder if Chief Sangenya
was shocked that she lost?

76
00:04:09,883 --> 00:04:10,884
What?

77
00:04:11,352 --> 00:04:13,320
Sanchi lost?

78
00:04:13,954 --> 00:04:16,857
It's because you helped Mr. Rusudo out!

79
00:04:16,924 --> 00:04:19,026
Oh, that Yazawa room?

80
00:04:19,093 --> 00:04:21,528
Yeah! Take that! Sanchi!

81
00:04:21,595 --> 00:04:23,964
Go to hell and become a better person!

82
00:04:24,031 --> 00:04:25,899
-You traitor!
-Shut up!

83
00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:27,167
What are you two talking about?

84
00:04:27,234 --> 00:04:28,869
You two are getting too hot.

85
00:04:28,936 --> 00:04:32,406
You're taking it out on them
since I fired you. Go home already.

86
00:04:32,473 --> 00:04:33,907
No lay off!

87
00:04:33,974 --> 00:04:35,342
I won't forgive you, Ms. Shirasu!

88
00:04:35,409 --> 00:04:36,744
I won't forgive Mr. Rusudo either!

89
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:38,746
Shut up, you Sanchi's dog!

90
00:04:38,812 --> 00:04:40,681
-I'm not a dog.
-Dog!

91
00:04:45,152 --> 00:04:46,153
Winner, Adachi!

92
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:56,296
Um…

93
00:04:57,164 --> 00:04:59,099
Has Mr. Rusudo come in yet?

94
00:04:59,566 --> 00:05:01,235
I don't think he'll come today.

95
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:19,319
The person Mr. Rusudo likes is Sanchi?

96
00:05:21,989 --> 00:05:25,159
I was just used by him?

97
00:05:35,636 --> 00:05:36,937
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

98
00:05:37,571 --> 00:05:39,373
Oh? Aren't you a bit late?

99
00:05:41,709 --> 00:05:43,977
You didn't sleep well last night?

100
00:05:45,079 --> 00:05:47,247
She didn't come home last night.

101
00:05:47,681 --> 00:05:51,051
What? Oh, Sangenya?

102
00:05:52,119 --> 00:05:55,355
Like I said, she's probably
at a hot spring or something.

103
00:05:55,823 --> 00:05:59,993
There's no way she would go missing.
It's Sangenya, after all!

104
00:06:00,627 --> 00:06:02,863
But she does have a difficult past.

105
00:06:04,298 --> 00:06:08,302
No one can tell what's going on
in her mind.

106
00:06:10,137 --> 00:06:13,207
Oh, that thing about
how she used to be homeless?

107
00:06:14,608 --> 00:06:17,778
I don't know the details
about that either.

108
00:06:18,445 --> 00:06:23,117
But I think she's carrying a lot of pain
and emotional scars.

109
00:06:23,484 --> 00:06:26,553
What? Does that mean Kenji Rusudo knows

110
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:31,225
Sangenya's big secret
her husband doesn't even know?

111
00:06:33,627 --> 00:06:39,333
It was weird when she went from
Kenji Rusudo to typing Mongolian names.

112
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:41,034
What do you think that was?

113
00:06:41,335 --> 00:06:43,737
Does it mean that Rusudo is actually
a Mongolian?

114
00:06:43,804 --> 00:06:45,506
Let's leave that for now.

115
00:06:46,006 --> 00:06:51,812
Maybe those two have something
unimaginable going on between them.

116
00:06:52,646 --> 00:06:55,215
Something unimaginable?

117
00:06:58,619 --> 00:06:59,820
I'm back.

118
00:07:00,354 --> 00:07:02,589
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

119
00:07:02,656 --> 00:07:05,559
Manager, it's better
to demolish that old house in Aoyama

120
00:07:05,626 --> 00:07:07,728
and sell just the land.

121
00:07:07,795 --> 00:07:11,965
The location is great,
but the exterior is just horrible.

122
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,834
Manager.

123
00:07:15,502 --> 00:07:17,137
Manager! Are you listening to me?

124
00:07:17,504 --> 00:07:21,141
Oh, I'm listening. That's the place
where the interior was remodeled, right?

125
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:25,112
Well, that was unnecessary.
It's hard to demolish it now.

126
00:07:25,179 --> 00:07:29,716
Oh that. Could you have your special
China Network of yours to handle it?

127
00:07:31,218 --> 00:07:32,920
This single family home

128
00:07:32,986 --> 00:07:36,557
has a central heating system. It's warm
in the winter, and cool during summer.

129
00:07:36,623 --> 00:07:38,559
It's a comfortable house all year round.

130
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:42,796
That's great, but its appearance
is not good.

131
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,731
I like that it's in Aoyama.

132
00:07:45,766 --> 00:07:48,435
Considering your budget
is about ¥60 million…

133
00:07:48,502 --> 00:07:51,839
I don't want a home
unless it looks good from the outside.

134
00:07:51,905 --> 00:07:53,407
-So you mean the exterior?
-Yes.

135
00:07:53,674 --> 00:07:58,078
When you come home tired from work,
that's the first thing you see.

136
00:07:58,145 --> 00:08:01,448
If it's not a nice exterior then
I wouldn't want to go home.

137
00:08:02,349 --> 00:08:04,985
If it looks nice, then I would
want to go home early too.

138
00:08:05,385 --> 00:08:08,789
I see. Is that how your wife feels too?

139
00:08:09,323 --> 00:08:11,725
She's not my wife. Right?

140
00:08:12,359 --> 00:08:14,328
We are engaged right now.

141
00:08:14,394 --> 00:08:16,663
Oh, excuse me.

142
00:08:16,730 --> 00:08:18,532
You think she's too beautiful
for me, right?

143
00:08:18,599 --> 00:08:21,268
Not at all, but she is beautiful.

144
00:08:21,335 --> 00:08:23,637
-I graduated from Tokyo University.
-What?

145
00:08:23,704 --> 00:08:25,038
Why do you think I went
to Tokyo University?

146
00:08:25,105 --> 00:08:26,073
Why?

147
00:08:26,139 --> 00:08:28,242
To get myself a beautiful wife.

148
00:08:28,308 --> 00:08:31,178
I look this way,
so I put in a lot of effort

149
00:08:31,245 --> 00:08:34,748
to enhance my worth.
Tokyo University was one of them.

150
00:08:35,682 --> 00:08:37,217
To marry a beautiful woman like her.

151
00:08:38,652 --> 00:08:40,320
You've heard of designer properties?

152
00:08:40,387 --> 00:08:43,156
Find a home that gets attention
from the pedestrians.

153
00:08:43,757 --> 00:08:44,992
This won't do.

154
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:47,995
I think funds are sufficient,

155
00:08:48,328 --> 00:08:50,964
but a single family designer's home
in Aoyama

156
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:54,668
might be a bit difficult.
If it could be in the suburbs?

157
00:08:54,735 --> 00:08:57,271
There's no point if it's out
in nowhere, even if it looks good.

158
00:08:58,171 --> 00:09:00,607
Then I'll search again.

159
00:09:00,674 --> 00:09:02,976
Thank you. By the way!

160
00:09:04,378 --> 00:09:05,379
This flyer?

161
00:09:06,179 --> 00:09:08,315
I got it downstairs just now,

162
00:09:08,682 --> 00:09:10,918
but did this Machi Sangenya

163
00:09:10,984 --> 00:09:13,287
graduate from
Midoricho First Elementary School?

164
00:09:15,989 --> 00:09:17,157
I'm not sure.

165
00:09:19,226 --> 00:09:23,430
I think she said her elementary school
was called Midori something.

166
00:09:23,864 --> 00:09:25,899
It must be her if her husband says so.

167
00:09:26,366 --> 00:09:28,735
This is Manchichi.
It brings back memories.

168
00:09:29,202 --> 00:09:30,404
Manchichi?

169
00:09:32,406 --> 00:09:35,309
That was her nickname
in elementary school. I was Tabeyan.

170
00:09:35,642 --> 00:09:38,578
Sangenya was called Manchichi?

171
00:09:38,912 --> 00:09:40,414
Well, she's cheerful, right?

172
00:09:41,081 --> 00:09:42,249
Cheerful?

173
00:09:44,885 --> 00:09:49,423
Mr. Tabe, your classmate Manchichi
may be a different person.

174
00:09:49,856 --> 00:09:51,591
By the way, her favorite phrase was "Go!"

175
00:09:51,658 --> 00:09:53,994
There is no doubt.
That is definitely Sangenya.

176
00:09:54,561 --> 00:09:59,299
She was popular. She made everyone
laugh with her jokes all day long.

177
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:03,070
This picture doesn't look quite like her
since she seems stuck up.

178
00:10:03,303 --> 00:10:05,038
I don't have any issue with you, Niwano,

179
00:10:05,105 --> 00:10:08,008
but if Manchichi works here,
I would like her to be my realtor.

180
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:11,645
Sangenya is on vacation right now.

181
00:10:12,279 --> 00:10:14,848
In that case, Niwano is fine for now.

182
00:10:15,282 --> 00:10:18,318
Please tell Manchichi I said "hello"
and that Tabeyan wanted to see her.

183
00:10:18,385 --> 00:10:19,386
Of course.

184
00:10:19,686 --> 00:10:22,322
I'll contact you once I find something
that meets your requests.

185
00:10:22,389 --> 00:10:23,223
See you.

186
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,835
MACHI SANGENYA
THERE IS NO PROPERTY I CAN'T SELL!

187
00:10:37,571 --> 00:10:39,006
Manchichi?

188
00:10:58,291 --> 00:11:02,329
Tokoshima! The way you react
is like Pavlov's dog!

189
00:11:03,530 --> 00:11:07,868
Isn't this music played for that purpose?

190
00:11:09,770 --> 00:11:10,771
See you.

191
00:11:11,872 --> 00:11:14,708
I shouldn't have said anything.

192
00:11:14,975 --> 00:11:16,209
I'm leaving too.

193
00:11:17,411 --> 00:11:19,579
-Well then, good bye.
-Good bye.

194
00:11:25,419 --> 00:11:30,257
Then I'll do the same, and leave too!

195
00:11:33,894 --> 00:11:35,796
I'm leaving too.

196
00:11:41,535 --> 00:11:43,136
Manager! Manager!

197
00:11:44,604 --> 00:11:45,605
Huh?

198
00:11:47,074 --> 00:11:48,308
Let's follow Mr. Adachi.

199
00:11:48,942 --> 00:11:49,810
What?

200
00:11:49,876 --> 00:11:52,679
I think we'll find Mr. Rusudo
if we follow Mr. Adachi.

201
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,548
If we find out who Mr. Rusudo is,

202
00:11:54,614 --> 00:11:56,550
then we'll know his relationship
with Chief Sangenya.

203
00:11:57,951 --> 00:12:02,322
What? Both Adachi and Sangenya
are my employees.

204
00:12:03,023 --> 00:12:04,524
I don't want to doubt them like that.

205
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:07,360
I see. Then I'll go by myself.

206
00:12:12,299 --> 00:12:13,400
WEST SHINJUKU SPORTS CENTER

207
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:14,968
CHEVALIER FENCING CLUB

208
00:12:23,210 --> 00:12:24,578
They're here! Mr. Rusudo is here too.

209
00:12:25,178 --> 00:12:26,179
What?

210
00:12:30,016 --> 00:12:32,052
So Mr. Adachi and Mr. Rusudo
meet here every day.

211
00:12:35,822 --> 00:12:37,624
They should be coming out soon.

212
00:12:38,258 --> 00:12:39,259
Quiet!

213
00:12:41,595 --> 00:12:42,896
Manager! There they are!

214
00:12:45,398 --> 00:12:46,800
They seem serious.

215
00:12:54,141 --> 00:12:57,010
Do you think information
is being leaked right now?

216
00:13:02,282 --> 00:13:03,750
He's adding salt to coffee.

217
00:13:04,851 --> 00:13:06,720
What does that mean?

218
00:13:07,687 --> 00:13:08,889
Who knows?

219
00:13:16,096 --> 00:13:17,164
Now they're laughing.

220
00:13:24,638 --> 00:13:26,072
-Well.
-Yes.

221
00:13:27,207 --> 00:13:29,609
Satoshi, thanks for today.

222
00:13:30,277 --> 00:13:31,378
Thank you.

223
00:13:34,915 --> 00:13:36,750
They look like a couple.

224
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:42,989
See you soon.

225
00:13:45,125 --> 00:13:47,460
Did he call him "Satoshi" right now?

226
00:13:47,527 --> 00:13:48,562
Who do we follow?

227
00:13:48,628 --> 00:13:50,063
You know which one!

228
00:13:52,399 --> 00:13:53,833
DEMOLITION OF OLD MIDORICHO

229
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:55,769
FIRST ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

230
00:14:45,819 --> 00:14:46,953
Wow!

231
00:14:50,991 --> 00:14:52,292
What are you doing here?

232
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:55,395
What are you doing here, Mr. Rusudo?

233
00:14:55,729 --> 00:14:57,664
I forgot something.

234
00:14:58,465 --> 00:14:59,933
Is this it?

235
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,568
Yes, thank you.

236
00:15:08,308 --> 00:15:11,645
Um, that's salt, again.

237
00:15:12,712 --> 00:15:13,713
Again?

238
00:15:14,681 --> 00:15:15,849
Oh, um, no.

239
00:15:17,517 --> 00:15:19,719
-Are you okay?
-I'm sorry.

240
00:15:21,888 --> 00:15:23,189
So…

241
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:27,527
What is your relationship with Sangenya?

242
00:15:32,732 --> 00:15:35,969
I admire Ms. Sangenya.

243
00:15:39,172 --> 00:15:44,811
That means that you admire
Chief Sangenya as a realtor, right?

244
00:15:44,878 --> 00:15:46,946
-That too…
-What else is there?

245
00:15:50,016 --> 00:15:51,017
Excuse me.

246
00:15:52,519 --> 00:15:55,555
Were you perhaps following me?

247
00:15:57,223 --> 00:16:01,995
When I almost added salt,
you said "again", right?

248
00:16:04,097 --> 00:16:05,198
I apologize.

249
00:16:05,665 --> 00:16:08,635
We were following you.
I know it was very immature of us,

250
00:16:08,702 --> 00:16:10,036
but I couldn't help it.

251
00:16:11,004 --> 00:16:12,238
I see.

252
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:16,042
Then I must tell you.

253
00:16:20,146 --> 00:16:21,414
I love her.

254
00:16:24,751 --> 00:16:26,653
You mean to say…

255
00:16:27,287 --> 00:16:31,458
you love Chief Sangenya's skills
as a realtor, right?

256
00:16:31,825 --> 00:16:34,861
We were in the same grade, and…

257
00:16:36,296 --> 00:16:39,332
I've loved Ms. Sangenya since then.

258
00:16:44,404 --> 00:16:45,739
Any other questions?

259
00:16:48,408 --> 00:16:49,909
No…

260
00:16:54,647 --> 00:16:55,849
Here.

261
00:17:01,454 --> 00:17:02,288
Oh?

262
00:17:04,891 --> 00:17:05,925
You push it.

263
00:17:08,495 --> 00:17:09,496
Thank you.

264
00:17:11,664 --> 00:17:15,602
She never told me
they were in the same grade.

265
00:17:16,669 --> 00:17:17,871
Oh, by the way,

266
00:17:18,238 --> 00:17:21,307
today's client, Mr. Tabe,
said he was in the same class too.

267
00:17:21,975 --> 00:17:23,209
Let's ask him.

268
00:17:23,543 --> 00:17:27,347
How would you ask him?
It's not appropriate either.

269
00:17:31,718 --> 00:17:33,086
-But let's go anyway.
-Yes.

270
00:17:33,486 --> 00:17:35,088
TABE

271
00:17:39,526 --> 00:17:41,528
What's going on?

272
00:17:41,795 --> 00:17:44,030
Sorry to visit you so late at night.

273
00:17:44,631 --> 00:17:47,901
We have something we want to
ask you, Mr. Tabe.

274
00:17:48,234 --> 00:17:49,235
Ask me what?

275
00:17:50,603 --> 00:17:53,339
This is the graduation album
from my elementary school.

276
00:17:54,140 --> 00:17:57,444
I don't recall anyone
named "Rusudo" though.

277
00:17:57,911 --> 00:17:59,379
That name is different,

278
00:18:00,413 --> 00:18:02,582
so I would remember if he was there.

279
00:18:02,649 --> 00:18:04,317
This is my class.

280
00:18:05,285 --> 00:18:06,453
GRADUATION ALBUM

281
00:18:06,519 --> 00:18:10,590
Ah! Chief Sangenya is cute!

282
00:18:10,657 --> 00:18:11,925
She's really cute, right?

283
00:18:12,325 --> 00:18:14,127
She used to smile like this, huh?

284
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:15,328
She doesn't anymore?

285
00:18:17,997 --> 00:18:21,267
She's smiling so brightly here.

286
00:18:22,035 --> 00:18:23,937
Look at this.

287
00:18:24,804 --> 00:18:26,539
Take a look at this. Go!

288
00:18:29,209 --> 00:18:30,710
She has a flag on her head.

289
00:18:30,777 --> 00:18:32,111
She was good with magic.

290
00:18:32,178 --> 00:18:33,246
-Wow.
-Really?

291
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:35,915
She has flags of nations
coming out of her mouth.

292
00:18:36,316 --> 00:18:39,018
Look. This is the class ranking
for different things.

293
00:18:39,419 --> 00:18:42,388
The number one class clown was Manchichi.

294
00:18:42,455 --> 00:18:44,924
-What?
-You're right.

295
00:18:46,092 --> 00:18:47,560
I see your name too, Mr. Tabe.

296
00:18:47,827 --> 00:18:49,596
You were ranked second in D and B ranking.

297
00:18:50,029 --> 00:18:52,265
-What is D and B?
-"Ditzy and Butt-ugly".

298
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,635
Well, you are in second.

299
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:58,605
Dojisuke, who ranked first,
is named Yoshio Sanpei,

300
00:18:58,671 --> 00:19:00,373
but he was number one without a doubt.

301
00:19:00,974 --> 00:19:02,609
See? This is Dojisuke.

302
00:19:04,611 --> 00:19:07,213
He resembles someone a bit…

303
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,581
I think Jack Nicholson.

304
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:11,951
Children are harsh.

305
00:19:12,018 --> 00:19:15,121
Yes, this ranking is a blemish in my past,

306
00:19:15,622 --> 00:19:19,859
but because of this, I moved to action.
I'm thankful for this ranking now.

307
00:19:23,196 --> 00:19:27,100
But I don't think this Rusudo guy
was in our grade.

308
00:19:29,068 --> 00:19:31,738
Maybe he's her classmate
from middle school or high school?

309
00:19:35,942 --> 00:19:37,110
I was surprised

310
00:19:38,044 --> 00:19:41,514
to see that Chief Sangenya's
childhood was like that.

311
00:19:42,482 --> 00:19:45,451
We've never seen her smile like that.

312
00:19:46,619 --> 00:19:48,755
Is it because a lot happened to her?

313
00:19:50,657 --> 00:19:53,092
The class clown Manchichi…

314
00:19:56,162 --> 00:19:57,163
Manager…

315
00:19:58,431 --> 00:20:02,168
Chief Sangenya doesn't smile
at home either?

316
00:20:03,336 --> 00:20:04,437
That's right.

317
00:20:05,405 --> 00:20:07,740
She doesn't say "morning" with a smile?

318
00:20:07,974 --> 00:20:09,576
She doesn't do that.

319
00:20:10,410 --> 00:20:12,211
Manager! Good morning.

320
00:20:12,478 --> 00:20:14,948
Manager! Dinner is ready!

321
00:20:15,148 --> 00:20:17,050
Manager! Let's get it on tonight!

322
00:20:18,251 --> 00:20:19,352
Like that?

323
00:20:19,419 --> 00:20:21,955
She says, "Let's get it on"?

324
00:20:23,189 --> 00:20:25,725
No, no, go to…

325
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:29,696
bed early tonight.
There's a meeting at 9:30 tomorrow.

326
00:20:29,762 --> 00:20:30,763
Don't be late!

327
00:20:31,064 --> 00:20:34,067
I know! That's our daily routine!

328
00:20:35,969 --> 00:20:37,270
Another one please.

329
00:20:37,637 --> 00:20:40,073
How could you show your face
when you just got fired?

330
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:41,574
How shameless.

331
00:20:41,941 --> 00:20:45,979
You shouldn't talk to a customer
like that!

332
00:20:46,045 --> 00:20:49,182
How about this one?
Company cafeteria server.

333
00:20:49,248 --> 00:20:53,987
Available 20 days per month,
four hours a day, and ¥1,500 an hour.

334
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:58,024
-The hourly rate is good.
-What? A server is so tiring.

335
00:20:58,291 --> 00:20:59,659
Don't be so picky!

336
00:20:59,926 --> 00:21:02,996
A receptionist at a beauty salon
won't work for you.

337
00:21:03,062 --> 00:21:03,896
Why not?

338
00:21:03,963 --> 00:21:05,898
They'll reject you based
on your appearance.

339
00:21:06,366 --> 00:21:07,667
Ouch!

340
00:21:08,501 --> 00:21:11,070
I don't want to work where it's all women.
Men need to be there.

341
00:21:11,337 --> 00:21:12,872
Don't be so picky.

342
00:21:12,939 --> 00:21:15,642
Pachinko hall staff.
No experience necessary.

343
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:18,611
Hourly rate is ¥1,300 to ¥2,125 an hour.

344
00:21:18,911 --> 00:21:23,016
What? I've been raised properly.
I can't work there.

345
00:21:23,082 --> 00:21:24,183
Don't be so picky!

346
00:21:25,351 --> 00:21:27,120
A bedrock bath massage.

347
00:21:27,186 --> 00:21:28,888
No certification necessary,
¥1,000 an hour.

348
00:21:28,955 --> 00:21:31,724
Bedrock bath? I hate heat!

349
00:21:31,791 --> 00:21:33,292
Ah! You sweat a lot.

350
00:21:33,359 --> 00:21:35,695
-Shut up!
-Ouch!

351
00:21:38,631 --> 00:21:39,632
You know,

352
00:21:39,966 --> 00:21:44,003
how could you drink so much
while the kids are with your mother?

353
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:47,407
Shut up! I'm giving that old hag
a reason to live!

354
00:21:47,674 --> 00:21:49,842
Mika, why don't you go home already?

355
00:21:49,909 --> 00:21:52,945
I heard kids are only cute for so long.

356
00:21:53,012 --> 00:21:55,615
There it is! Kokoro's lecture!

357
00:21:56,015 --> 00:21:58,518
You're so cocky and uppity
just because you're somewhat cute.

358
00:21:58,851 --> 00:22:01,888
Most good looking people
have horrible personalities,

359
00:22:01,954 --> 00:22:04,557
except me. It's the same for that woman.

360
00:22:04,957 --> 00:22:05,992
That woman?

361
00:22:06,225 --> 00:22:08,795
Sangenjaya!

362
00:22:09,162 --> 00:22:11,664
She abused me just because
she's beautiful.

363
00:22:11,731 --> 00:22:15,201
My life is in ruins because of that woman!

364
00:22:15,635 --> 00:22:18,571
I was supposed to get married
to MR. Adachi,

365
00:22:18,638 --> 00:22:22,141
but instead I got married to this
ugly one!

366
00:22:23,976 --> 00:22:25,912
I'm glad you guys divorced.

367
00:22:26,646 --> 00:22:27,880
I'm going home now.

368
00:22:27,947 --> 00:22:29,716
Go home! Go! Go!

369
00:22:30,016 --> 00:22:33,386
You short-legged frump with weird hair!
Correct your articulation!

370
00:22:33,619 --> 00:22:37,023
I'm closing now, so you go home too!

371
00:22:37,090 --> 00:22:39,058
Here's your bill for today.

372
00:22:39,759 --> 00:22:42,395
Whoa! Could you charge it?

373
00:22:42,462 --> 00:22:43,796
No way!

374
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:48,634
Mr. Niwano!

375
00:22:50,503 --> 00:22:51,571
Thank you for coming.

376
00:22:51,804 --> 00:22:53,906
Sorry for showing up like that
the other day.

377
00:22:53,973 --> 00:22:54,874
No problem.

378
00:22:55,541 --> 00:22:57,643
I would like to show you
this property today.

379
00:22:58,578 --> 00:23:02,448
I guess this is as good as it gets
for ¥60 million in Aoyama.

380
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:06,886
The white walls look great against
the blue skies. It's very attractive.

381
00:23:07,153 --> 00:23:09,622
It's not the exterior I would want
to go home to…

382
00:23:12,191 --> 00:23:14,594
This is the main bedroom.

383
00:23:17,697 --> 00:23:21,334
There's storage in the attic too.

384
00:23:23,369 --> 00:23:25,938
I think this is very useful.

385
00:23:28,207 --> 00:23:30,009
Nana, if you have any requests,
say it, okay?

386
00:23:32,211 --> 00:23:37,683
I'm fine, as long as I'm with you, Ryuji.

387
00:23:40,253 --> 00:23:42,288
What a wonderful fiancée!

388
00:23:42,722 --> 00:23:45,124
Isn't she nice and modest
although she's beautiful?

389
00:23:45,191 --> 00:23:46,192
She really is.

390
00:23:47,660 --> 00:23:51,397
The interior is nice,
but that exterior didn't click.

391
00:23:55,268 --> 00:23:57,236
Ah, this is from work.

392
00:24:01,207 --> 00:24:02,475
-Um…
-Yes?

393
00:24:02,875 --> 00:24:05,444
-There is one thing I want to check…
-Yes?

394
00:24:06,078 --> 00:24:09,682
Does the restroom have a lock?

395
00:24:12,885 --> 00:24:14,887
Let's take a look then.

396
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:21,594
It locks.

397
00:24:22,895 --> 00:24:23,963
I'm glad.

398
00:24:24,697 --> 00:24:27,700
A lock for the restroom
is the only request I have.

399
00:24:29,268 --> 00:24:31,637
Please take a look at the bathroom too.

400
00:24:33,206 --> 00:24:34,473
Ah…

401
00:24:34,674 --> 00:24:37,243
This property's bathroom
is very substantial.

402
00:24:38,277 --> 00:24:40,513
When you push this button,
it becomes a steam bath.

403
00:24:45,885 --> 00:24:47,520
STEAM BATH

404
00:24:49,989 --> 00:24:52,458
Mr. Niwano, no! no! Stop it.

405
00:24:52,525 --> 00:24:54,160
I am so sorry!

406
00:24:54,527 --> 00:24:56,696
Maybe it just means
that this house isn't meant to be.

407
00:25:01,167 --> 00:25:04,804
I'm going home now.

408
00:25:05,705 --> 00:25:06,839
What's the matter?

409
00:25:06,906 --> 00:25:09,442
My make-up came off.

410
00:25:09,909 --> 00:25:11,444
That's not important.

411
00:25:11,944 --> 00:25:14,213
-But…
-You don't need to hide it.

412
00:25:14,914 --> 00:25:16,415
You are beautiful.

413
00:25:23,890 --> 00:25:25,224
-What was that?
-I don't know.

414
00:25:25,591 --> 00:25:26,859
Who are you?

415
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:28,728
I'm Nana.

416
00:25:28,794 --> 00:25:30,529
Stop lying! Nana's face is not like that.

417
00:25:32,632 --> 00:25:33,666
What's going on here?

418
00:25:35,268 --> 00:25:36,269
My make-up…

419
00:25:37,436 --> 00:25:39,171
I had make-up on.

420
00:25:39,572 --> 00:25:40,806
Make-up changes a face that much?

421
00:25:41,340 --> 00:25:43,776
Lately, you can do that.

422
00:25:43,843 --> 00:25:45,044
You can double the size of your eyes?

423
00:25:45,111 --> 00:25:46,345
Lately, you can do that.

424
00:25:46,412 --> 00:25:48,915
No way! You were fooling me?

425
00:25:49,248 --> 00:25:51,851
I never would have gone out
with you if I knew you were ugly!

426
00:25:51,918 --> 00:25:54,587
Mr. Tabe, that's saying a bit too much…

427
00:25:54,654 --> 00:25:56,656
First of all, the fact
that you hid your ugly face

428
00:25:56,722 --> 00:25:58,424
makes you ugly on the inside too!

429
00:25:59,225 --> 00:26:01,227
I didn't want you to hate me, Ryuji.

430
00:26:01,460 --> 00:26:02,929
I've told you several times.

431
00:26:02,995 --> 00:26:06,265
I've worked hard all my life
to marry a beautiful woman.

432
00:26:06,332 --> 00:26:09,936
If I marry an ugly one,
then my life plan will be ruined!

433
00:26:10,536 --> 00:26:12,138
All my efforts have been wasted.

434
00:26:12,471 --> 00:26:15,341
-Mr. Niwano! Please apologize to Ryuji.
-What?

435
00:26:15,408 --> 00:26:16,809
Please apologize with me!

436
00:26:16,876 --> 00:26:19,745
Yes! Ta… Mr. Tabe…

437
00:26:19,812 --> 00:26:24,717
I'm sorry that this happened,
since I pushed the remote control switch.

438
00:26:24,784 --> 00:26:26,719
Please calm down.

439
00:26:26,919 --> 00:26:29,488
I'll ask you then.
Could you marry that face?

440
00:26:33,326 --> 00:26:35,561
If you can, marry Nana for me then.

441
00:26:35,828 --> 00:26:37,697
Ms. Nana loves you, Mr. Tabe.

442
00:26:37,763 --> 00:26:42,268
See? Nana, your make-up
is like a trick art.

443
00:26:42,468 --> 00:26:45,371
I'm not nice enough to laugh
and forget about this whole thing.

444
00:26:45,738 --> 00:26:48,174
In any case, unless I marry someone
beautiful, it's pointless!

445
00:26:48,841 --> 00:26:50,109
Our engagement is off!

446
00:27:00,686 --> 00:27:05,324
Mr. Tabe, it's true that Ms. Nana
shouldn't have tricked you,

447
00:27:05,624 --> 00:27:07,193
but aren't you being a little too mean?

448
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:09,528
Appearance isn't everything for us humans.

449
00:27:09,895 --> 00:27:11,364
You do have a point,

450
00:27:12,431 --> 00:27:15,735
but not everything can be settled
by being nice. It's all over.

451
00:27:21,774 --> 00:27:22,775
Chief Sangenya?

452
00:27:25,144 --> 00:27:26,445
Manchichi?

453
00:27:26,879 --> 00:27:29,482
Yes, I'm Manchichi!

454
00:27:30,082 --> 00:27:33,552
Chief Sangenya, where have you been?
Everyone was worried.

455
00:27:33,753 --> 00:27:36,989
Tabeyan, I will sell you a house.

456
00:27:37,456 --> 00:27:42,595
No, I would like to buy from you,
but things are complicated now.

457
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:44,497
Even so, I'll still sell you a house.

458
00:27:44,964 --> 00:27:47,700
There is no house I can't sell.

459
00:27:48,901 --> 00:27:50,002
-Niwano!
-Yes!

460
00:27:50,069 --> 00:27:53,672
Please take Tabeyan home.
I'll go after Ms. Nana.

461
00:27:55,608 --> 00:27:58,144
Was that really Manchichi?

462
00:27:58,911 --> 00:28:00,613
That was Manchichi.

463
00:28:01,414 --> 00:28:04,150
Manchichi has changed a lot.

464
00:28:16,062 --> 00:28:17,296
Thank you for waiting.

465
00:28:18,130 --> 00:28:19,131
No problem.

466
00:28:20,166 --> 00:28:22,668
I'm sorry to bother you at home.

467
00:28:23,736 --> 00:28:27,273
Ryuji has told me a lot about you,
Manchichi.

468
00:28:28,507 --> 00:28:31,177
You really are beautiful.

469
00:28:31,544 --> 00:28:32,678
Thank you very much.

470
00:28:34,046 --> 00:28:38,818
By the way, Ms. Nana.
Do you really love Mr. Tabe?

471
00:28:39,685 --> 00:28:41,854
Do I love him?

472
00:28:42,621 --> 00:28:45,991
He went to Tokyo University
although he's that ugly.

473
00:28:46,058 --> 00:28:48,027
He got a job at a bank
although he's that ugly,

474
00:28:48,094 --> 00:28:51,097
and he got promoted the fastest
although he's that ugly.

475
00:28:51,664 --> 00:28:54,867
I think he really is a star
of the world of uglies.

476
00:28:55,601 --> 00:28:56,869
You are quite blunt.

477
00:28:57,470 --> 00:29:01,307
I've learned from him
that if you try hard,

478
00:29:01,574 --> 00:29:04,310
you can shine no matter how ugly you are.

479
00:29:05,277 --> 00:29:08,280
That's why I respect him
from the bottom of my heart.

480
00:29:09,148 --> 00:29:12,318
If that respect is the same as love,

481
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:14,987
then I think it is love.

482
00:29:15,855 --> 00:29:16,856
I see.

483
00:29:17,456 --> 00:29:21,994
And… I saw his "Determination Notebook".

484
00:29:22,495 --> 00:29:23,596
Determination Notebook?

485
00:29:24,196 --> 00:29:26,499
It's like his diary.

486
00:29:27,133 --> 00:29:29,635
"A good looking colleague stole my job".

487
00:29:29,702 --> 00:29:31,871
"We had similar results. I'm disappointed,

488
00:29:32,238 --> 00:29:33,572
but I won't give up".

489
00:29:34,173 --> 00:29:35,608
"I'll work hard although I'm ugly".

490
00:29:36,108 --> 00:29:38,711
"I'll work hard to be in first place".

491
00:29:40,312 --> 00:29:43,916
Those were the words he wrote.
Aren't they wonderful?

492
00:29:45,084 --> 00:29:49,188
No matter how harsh his words were,
I can't hate him,

493
00:29:50,289 --> 00:29:52,458
because I saw
his "Determination Notebook".

494
00:29:53,559 --> 00:29:57,763
He's working hard going against
his fate of being ugly.

495
00:29:58,397 --> 00:30:01,500
I really like that about him,

496
00:30:02,768 --> 00:30:05,571
but I think it's over now.

497
00:30:07,373 --> 00:30:08,407
With all due respect,

498
00:30:09,441 --> 00:30:12,344
I will get you two back together.

499
00:30:13,212 --> 00:30:14,079
What?

500
00:30:14,313 --> 00:30:16,982
And I will sell you two a house.

501
00:30:18,784 --> 00:30:20,386
Your confidence is amazing.

502
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:24,757
Beautiful people certainly are different.

503
00:30:27,293 --> 00:30:28,294
Another one please.

504
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:29,762
Are you okay, Mr. Tabe?

505
00:30:30,629 --> 00:30:33,499
-You think I'm an idiot, right?
-Of course not.

506
00:30:33,933 --> 00:30:36,001
You are quite good looking too.

507
00:30:36,468 --> 00:30:38,737
You must have been favored all your life.

508
00:30:38,804 --> 00:30:40,005
I don't think so.

509
00:30:40,072 --> 00:30:42,741
When you are favored,
then you just don't see it.

510
00:30:43,409 --> 00:30:44,577
When I was in kindergarten,

511
00:30:45,211 --> 00:30:47,880
there was this good looking
brat called Ren.

512
00:30:48,214 --> 00:30:52,284
I was running with him, and we both fell.

513
00:30:52,685 --> 00:30:56,322
Then the kindergarten teacher came,
and what do you think she said?

514
00:30:56,755 --> 00:30:59,191
-I don't know.
-I don't know.

515
00:31:00,125 --> 00:31:01,827
She asked, "Are you okay, Ren?"

516
00:31:03,095 --> 00:31:05,264
She only gave Ren a hug!

517
00:31:06,398 --> 00:31:09,501
Then after a while
she asked, "Are you okay too, Ryuji?"

518
00:31:10,269 --> 00:31:11,704
She said, "too"! I was an afterthought!

519
00:31:12,338 --> 00:31:13,339
Ah…

520
00:31:14,373 --> 00:31:16,809
My mother and father are ugly too.

521
00:31:17,476 --> 00:31:21,714
I want to end the ugly lineage with me.

522
00:31:22,047 --> 00:31:27,186
That's why I wanted to marry a beauty
to change my ugly family's DNA.

523
00:31:28,854 --> 00:31:33,559
That's why I studied harder than others
to go to Tokyo University and all.

524
00:31:35,361 --> 00:31:37,896
You would do everything to marry a beauty?

525
00:31:38,731 --> 00:31:39,565
Yes.

526
00:31:39,865 --> 00:31:44,837
It's so sweet that Ms. Nana wanted
to be pretty for you, Mr. Tabe.

527
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:47,539
You say that since it's not you.

528
00:31:47,606 --> 00:31:51,610
I'm so disgusted that I was
fooled by that ugly face!

529
00:31:52,711 --> 00:31:53,979
It's a fraud! A fraud!

530
00:31:54,346 --> 00:31:58,083
But what's different about
making an effort to look pretty,

531
00:31:58,150 --> 00:32:02,588
and working hard to attend
a good college and get a good job?

532
00:32:05,691 --> 00:32:06,725
It's the same.

533
00:32:11,897 --> 00:32:13,666
Our company is no joke.

534
00:32:13,999 --> 00:32:15,434
It seriously is no joke.

535
00:32:15,501 --> 00:32:17,903
Manager is so timid.

536
00:32:18,237 --> 00:32:20,606
He needs to say something more impactful!

537
00:32:21,006 --> 00:32:23,809
Chief Adachi thinks he's good looking,

538
00:32:23,876 --> 00:32:25,711
but lately, he's been non-existent.

539
00:32:26,812 --> 00:32:28,814
Maybe I'll change jobs.

540
00:32:29,281 --> 00:32:30,849
You have nowhere to go.

541
00:32:31,183 --> 00:32:32,484
What do you mean?

542
00:32:32,785 --> 00:32:35,354
Ah! Isn't that Adachi?

543
00:32:35,654 --> 00:32:37,122
-One whisky with water please.
-Yes, sir.

544
00:32:38,757 --> 00:32:39,758
Hello!

545
00:32:40,125 --> 00:32:43,662
What's going on?
You aren't going to your usual place?

546
00:32:44,129 --> 00:32:45,698
That Chichin-something place.

547
00:32:46,065 --> 00:32:47,966
Sometimes I want to drink alone.

548
00:32:48,300 --> 00:32:52,571
Me too. Dealing with work
after hours is impossible for me!

549
00:32:54,073 --> 00:32:55,607
Wait, are you two dating?

550
00:32:56,275 --> 00:32:58,877
Love and dating are too much work.

551
00:32:58,944 --> 00:33:01,180
We are the disinterested type.

552
00:33:01,580 --> 00:33:02,848
What is the disinterested type?

553
00:33:03,315 --> 00:33:05,851
It's like ahead of the passive type?

554
00:33:07,019 --> 00:33:08,520
You won't even fall in love?

555
00:33:09,688 --> 00:33:11,223
You do, Mr. Adachi?

556
00:33:12,825 --> 00:33:14,593
Leave me alone.

557
00:33:16,295 --> 00:33:17,696
What did you want to talk to me about?

558
00:33:20,199 --> 00:33:21,200
Well…

559
00:33:23,869 --> 00:33:27,373
Why are you so interested in Sanchi?

560
00:33:30,175 --> 00:33:31,410
Did you perhaps…

561
00:33:32,511 --> 00:33:35,047
use me?

562
00:33:36,515 --> 00:33:38,984
Did you use me to get close to Sanchi?

563
00:33:40,386 --> 00:33:43,322
I guess in certain ways, I did.

564
00:33:45,624 --> 00:33:51,397
It's true that I thought I may hear things
about Ms. Sangenya through you.

565
00:33:55,367 --> 00:33:56,368
I'm sorry.

566
00:33:58,804 --> 00:34:04,743
But Satoshi, you are
very special to me now too.

567
00:34:10,282 --> 00:34:12,518
-Really?
-Really.

568
00:34:15,788 --> 00:34:16,789
Really?

569
00:34:17,256 --> 00:34:18,257
Really.

570
00:34:22,327 --> 00:34:23,328
What's the matter?

571
00:34:24,129 --> 00:34:26,398
Whether you have someone special or not

572
00:34:26,732 --> 00:34:29,168
will affect how abundant your life is.

573
00:34:30,302 --> 00:34:34,773
"Someone special" is just
a convenient word!

574
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:37,576
That's something you say
to someone you don't care about.

575
00:34:38,677 --> 00:34:40,212
Don't say that!

576
00:34:41,914 --> 00:34:43,081
-I'm sorry.
-Sorry.

577
00:34:47,586 --> 00:34:49,922
DETERMINATION NOTEBOOK

578
00:34:55,928 --> 00:34:58,630
"A very beautiful woman agreed
to go out with me.

579
00:34:59,731 --> 00:35:00,933
Her name is Nana.

580
00:35:01,700 --> 00:35:03,635
She's very kind and modest.

581
00:35:05,504 --> 00:35:07,539
I'm glad I worked hard.

582
00:35:16,982 --> 00:35:19,151
MAKE-UP REMOVAL WIPE

583
00:35:29,761 --> 00:35:30,762
Yes?

584
00:35:35,067 --> 00:35:36,068
Manchichi?

585
00:35:36,668 --> 00:35:38,370
May I come in?

586
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:43,342
What's with all that stuff?

587
00:35:45,878 --> 00:35:47,813
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

588
00:35:53,852 --> 00:35:56,588
-Good morning.
-Wow! You were here?

589
00:35:59,691 --> 00:36:03,996
Well, Niwano said you showed up
at the property yesterday,

590
00:36:04,496 --> 00:36:08,233
so I was waiting for you at home.
Why didn't you come home?

591
00:36:08,467 --> 00:36:10,102
It's to sell a house.

592
00:36:10,402 --> 00:36:13,705
I'm sure it was,
but I was worried about you.

593
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:16,575
I told you before
that since I am your wife,

594
00:36:16,642 --> 00:36:19,645
you are the only person I'd go back to.

595
00:36:21,980 --> 00:36:24,583
It's been a while,
so I prepared breakfast.

596
00:36:25,417 --> 00:36:26,418
What?

597
00:36:34,059 --> 00:36:35,093
It's delicious.

598
00:36:35,661 --> 00:36:36,828
Thank you very much.

599
00:36:38,463 --> 00:36:39,898
Where did you get this food?

600
00:36:40,232 --> 00:36:41,733
I made it at the office kitchenette.

601
00:36:42,034 --> 00:36:44,503
So it's all sort of haphazard. I'm sorry.

602
00:36:44,570 --> 00:36:46,705
Oh, it's very delicious.

603
00:36:47,639 --> 00:36:49,741
At home, instead of a full course meal,

604
00:36:49,808 --> 00:36:54,279
I'd like these rolled eggs, miso soup,
and natto for breakfast.

605
00:36:55,147 --> 00:36:56,315
I got it.

606
00:36:56,748 --> 00:36:58,650
Oh, I'm not complaining.

607
00:36:58,717 --> 00:36:59,985
It's just a little request.

608
00:37:00,419 --> 00:37:03,655
I will grant your little request.

609
00:37:09,528 --> 00:37:14,132
By the way, I saw your graduation album
at Mr. Tabeyan's place.

610
00:37:16,335 --> 00:37:19,237
You were ranked first as the class clown.

611
00:37:22,174 --> 00:37:25,444
I was so surprised to see you
with such a cute smile on your face.

612
00:37:28,046 --> 00:37:29,448
You want to see me smile?

613
00:37:30,616 --> 00:37:33,518
Well, it's just that
I've never seen it before.

614
00:37:40,158 --> 00:37:42,427
Are you going to show me?

615
00:37:43,829 --> 00:37:45,664
If you insist.

616
00:37:47,032 --> 00:37:49,401
Then I insist.

617
00:37:50,535 --> 00:37:52,638
Then, I will show you.

618
00:37:55,307 --> 00:37:57,342
I'm getting nervous.

619
00:37:58,410 --> 00:37:59,411
Here I go.

620
00:38:13,692 --> 00:38:16,261
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

621
00:38:16,328 --> 00:38:18,296
Do you smell natto?

622
00:38:20,666 --> 00:38:21,667
Really?

623
00:38:24,636 --> 00:38:25,704
He is here.

624
00:38:26,371 --> 00:38:28,140
Tabeyan, good morning.

625
00:38:28,940 --> 00:38:31,176
Manchichi, I have no intention
of buying a house now.

626
00:38:31,443 --> 00:38:34,546
I will show you the perfect house
for you and Ms. Nana.

627
00:38:34,613 --> 00:38:36,648
Like I said, I'm not getting
married anymore.

628
00:38:36,715 --> 00:38:38,617
Manchichi, you don't listen
to others anymore.

629
00:38:41,186 --> 00:38:45,323
Manchichi, since you are beautiful,
you probably don't get it,

630
00:38:45,657 --> 00:38:47,559
but appearance
is a pretty important matter.

631
00:38:48,360 --> 00:38:50,162
Since I now know that Nana is ugly,

632
00:38:50,395 --> 00:38:53,398
I can't continue to like her anymore,

633
00:38:53,465 --> 00:38:56,201
and that ugly face is stuck in my head.
I'm scared to see her.

634
00:38:56,735 --> 00:39:00,706
You and Nana are similar in that
you guys only care about appearances.

635
00:39:01,273 --> 00:39:03,575
That's not something to
be ashamed of either.

636
00:39:04,976 --> 00:39:06,678
Appearance is everything!

637
00:39:07,245 --> 00:39:09,748
It's the same
for people's faces and houses!

638
00:39:10,949 --> 00:39:12,217
Please come with me.

639
00:39:17,756 --> 00:39:20,058
Manchichi, what is this?

640
00:39:20,726 --> 00:39:22,360
This is the recommended house for you.

641
00:39:22,794 --> 00:39:23,762
Are you kidding me?

642
00:39:24,362 --> 00:39:27,199
Yeah, it's in Aoyama,
but this is a run-down house.

643
00:39:27,399 --> 00:39:29,434
Let's go in for now. Go ahead.

644
00:39:29,901 --> 00:39:32,971
-I won't see it.
-Don't say that. Go ahead.

645
00:39:33,171 --> 00:39:34,239
I said, I won't see it.

646
00:39:34,306 --> 00:39:35,574
-Go ahead!
-Yes!

647
00:39:38,210 --> 00:39:39,411
Go ahead.

648
00:39:51,590 --> 00:39:52,691
What do you think?

649
00:39:58,997 --> 00:40:02,067
It's nice. It's really nice.

650
00:40:03,001 --> 00:40:05,637
I don't know why,
but the whole room is shining brightly.

651
00:40:06,271 --> 00:40:07,873
This meets your budget too.

652
00:40:08,173 --> 00:40:09,508
This is wonderful.

653
00:40:11,576 --> 00:40:13,145
-But…
-But…?

654
00:40:14,946 --> 00:40:16,148
With an exterior like that…

655
00:40:17,949 --> 00:40:20,051
Because of that exterior,

656
00:40:20,118 --> 00:40:22,154
this interior looks even more wonderful.

657
00:40:22,721 --> 00:40:25,023
If this house's exterior was beautiful,

658
00:40:25,090 --> 00:40:27,058
then this house would just
be a regular nice house.

659
00:40:27,626 --> 00:40:29,528
But because of that exterior,

660
00:40:29,594 --> 00:40:33,231
this house has become a wonderful
and special house.

661
00:40:33,732 --> 00:40:34,933
Is that really so?

662
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:38,804
Tabeyan, do you remember
the restaurant near our school?

663
00:40:39,204 --> 00:40:41,273
Ah, that place that's messy but delicious.

664
00:40:41,339 --> 00:40:43,575
I went there recently.

665
00:40:43,642 --> 00:40:45,510
It is still messy,

666
00:40:45,911 --> 00:40:48,713
and it is still busy.

667
00:40:49,214 --> 00:40:52,717
The reason is the same.
Compared to a regular place,

668
00:40:52,784 --> 00:40:56,188
a messy yet delicious place
becomes people's favorite place.

669
00:40:56,655 --> 00:41:01,426
You can feel superior by thinking
you know what true value is.

670
00:41:02,227 --> 00:41:03,161
You might be right.

671
00:41:03,361 --> 00:41:05,964
This is what you call
a "contrasting charm".

672
00:41:07,532 --> 00:41:08,667
Contrasting charm?

673
00:41:10,669 --> 00:41:14,472
-The same goes for Ms. Nana too.
-What do you mean?

674
00:41:15,507 --> 00:41:18,810
Ms. Nana's bare face
is stuck in your head,

675
00:41:19,277 --> 00:41:21,246
but since you know how she really looks,

676
00:41:21,546 --> 00:41:24,316
Ms. Nana with make-up
will seem even more beautiful.

677
00:41:25,183 --> 00:41:26,852
-I'm not sure about that one.
-She will!

678
00:41:27,285 --> 00:41:31,890
Tabeyan knows not just the surface,
but her true self as well.

679
00:41:32,190 --> 00:41:35,427
Because of that, you will feel more
affection towards her.

680
00:41:35,727 --> 00:41:39,264
You get excited knowing
that you know something others don't.

681
00:41:40,098 --> 00:41:42,701
-Excited?
-Yes! Excited!

682
00:41:43,935 --> 00:41:45,837
-Niwano!
-Yes!

683
00:41:51,243 --> 00:41:53,445
What? What's going on?

684
00:41:53,678 --> 00:41:55,347
Ready go!

685
00:42:07,359 --> 00:42:08,360
Nana?

686
00:42:09,261 --> 00:42:12,664
No, please stop. Stop!

687
00:42:12,731 --> 00:42:14,566
Don't look away, Tabeyan!

688
00:42:17,202 --> 00:42:18,270
Ms. Nana, go!

689
00:42:33,985 --> 00:42:35,153
What do you think?

690
00:42:37,822 --> 00:42:42,193
She's beautiful. She seems
so much more beautiful than usual.

691
00:42:43,428 --> 00:42:46,765
This is Ms. Nana's charm.

692
00:42:48,266 --> 00:42:49,501
This is "contrasting charm"!

693
00:42:49,567 --> 00:42:51,202
So this is "contrasting charm"!

694
00:42:52,237 --> 00:42:57,676
This contrast will make your life
more meaningful and wonderful.

695
00:43:03,648 --> 00:43:04,516
Nana.

696
00:43:05,917 --> 00:43:10,522
Ryuji, could you once again

697
00:43:12,924 --> 00:43:18,697
love this fake face of mine?

698
00:43:19,698 --> 00:43:20,899
It's not fake.

699
00:43:23,635 --> 00:43:27,105
That face is also you, Nana.

700
00:43:31,109 --> 00:43:32,177
I've got them.

701
00:43:33,378 --> 00:43:35,180
Tabeyan! Ms. Nana,

702
00:43:36,614 --> 00:43:40,618
will you purchase this house
for ¥65 million?

703
00:43:42,387 --> 00:43:43,388
I'll buy it.

704
00:43:44,122 --> 00:43:45,190
Nana!

705
00:43:45,256 --> 00:43:46,324
Ryuji!

706
00:43:49,427 --> 00:43:51,029
-Niwano!
-Yes!

707
00:43:51,930 --> 00:43:53,298
The application form.

708
00:43:59,504 --> 00:44:01,072
It's the eighth floor! The eighth!

709
00:44:01,406 --> 00:44:03,141
It's room 88…

710
00:44:05,043 --> 00:44:06,478
I see, so it won't do.

711
00:44:08,179 --> 00:44:10,215
Manager! Oh, I messed up.

712
00:44:10,281 --> 00:44:14,219
Manager! The Chinese customers'
shopping spree is over!

713
00:44:14,285 --> 00:44:17,989
I see. I think I'm getting a fever,

714
00:44:18,056 --> 00:44:19,491
so I'm going to the hospital.

715
00:44:19,557 --> 00:44:21,593
You should get medication soon.
I hope you feel better.

716
00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:24,429
If it's the flu, then it's not cool.

717
00:44:25,563 --> 00:44:27,699
PRESCRIPTION

718
00:44:28,066 --> 00:44:30,535
Thank you for waiting, Mr. Yoshio Sanpei.

719
00:44:30,602 --> 00:44:33,605
Your medication is ready.
Mr. Yoshio Sanpei.

720
00:44:34,506 --> 00:44:36,408
-You are Mr. Yoshio Sanpei?
-Yes.

721
00:44:36,474 --> 00:44:38,543
This is your usual medication.
You know the directions?

722
00:44:38,610 --> 00:44:40,912
It's ¥2,950.

723
00:44:43,281 --> 00:44:44,282
Thank you.

724
00:44:46,418 --> 00:44:47,419
What?

725
00:44:50,555 --> 00:44:52,590
Yoshio Sanpei?

726
00:44:53,625 --> 00:44:54,726
What's D and B?

727
00:44:54,793 --> 00:44:55,994
"Ditzy and Butt-ugly".

728
00:44:56,227 --> 00:44:58,797
Dojisuke, who ranked first,
is named Yoshio Sanpei,

729
00:44:58,863 --> 00:45:00,532
but he was number one without a doubt.

730
00:45:19,050 --> 00:45:20,985
DEMOLITION OF OLD MIDORI
FIRST ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

731
00:45:49,981 --> 00:45:53,017
Thank you for contacting me.

732
00:45:54,919 --> 00:45:58,423
You are the man
who stole two house sales from me.

733
00:45:59,824 --> 00:46:04,129
I investigated Kenji Rusudo
while I was on paid vacation.

734
00:46:07,298 --> 00:46:10,201
You are Yoshio, right?

735
00:46:11,603 --> 00:46:12,837
You are Yoshio Sanpei.

736
00:46:17,142 --> 00:46:18,843
Why did you change your face?

737
00:46:24,983 --> 00:46:28,186
I wanted to see you again
as a different person.

738
00:46:30,288 --> 00:46:32,257
Is that why you changed your name?

739
00:46:33,525 --> 00:46:34,526
Yes.

740
00:46:38,930 --> 00:46:39,964
Manchichi…

741
00:46:41,466 --> 00:46:43,168
your seat was there,

742
00:46:44,302 --> 00:46:45,737
and my seat was here.

743
00:46:48,273 --> 00:46:49,607
When we were in elementary school,

744
00:46:52,010 --> 00:46:55,079
I was fat, short,

745
00:46:55,747 --> 00:46:56,748
and poor.

746
00:46:58,349 --> 00:47:02,086
I was bullied
and was nicknamed "Dojisuke",

747
00:47:02,554 --> 00:47:05,190
but someone delivered gyoza
to my home every week.

748
00:47:06,357 --> 00:47:08,426
Who was delivering it to me?

749
00:47:09,260 --> 00:47:12,163
I hid and waited to see who would show up,

750
00:47:13,731 --> 00:47:17,235
but I could never figure out who it was.

751
00:47:17,969 --> 00:47:18,970
Oh!

752
00:47:22,473 --> 00:47:24,442
One summer, during a swimming class,

753
00:47:25,710 --> 00:47:29,180
I drowned since I wasn't good at swimming.

754
00:47:31,883 --> 00:47:32,884
Then…

755
00:47:33,585 --> 00:47:36,955
the one who found me close
to losing my consciousness

756
00:47:38,356 --> 00:47:41,926
was the popular girl of the class,
Manchichi.

757
00:47:44,095 --> 00:47:46,064
Manchichi dived into the pool,

758
00:47:46,898 --> 00:47:48,233
pulled me out,

759
00:47:49,534 --> 00:47:51,169
and gave me mouth-to-mouth resuscitation.

760
00:47:52,904 --> 00:47:54,539
That mouth-to-mouth resuscitation…

761
00:47:58,876 --> 00:48:00,645
Tasted like that gyoza.

762
00:48:05,183 --> 00:48:07,185
Although my mind wasn't clear,

763
00:48:08,553 --> 00:48:10,021
I was certain…

764
00:48:11,222 --> 00:48:16,828
That Manchichi was the one
who was delivering gyoza every week.

765
00:48:20,898 --> 00:48:21,899
But…

766
00:48:24,335 --> 00:48:27,372
sometime during the second year
of high school,

767
00:48:28,940 --> 00:48:33,911
Manchichi suddenly disappeared.

768
00:48:34,979 --> 00:48:38,816
Then Manchichi…

769
00:48:40,518 --> 00:48:41,953
became homeless.

770
00:48:44,155 --> 00:48:46,257
I asked Manchichi,

771
00:48:47,392 --> 00:48:48,826
who was shivering in the park,

772
00:48:51,329 --> 00:48:52,330
if there is anything

773
00:48:53,498 --> 00:48:54,699
that you want.

774
00:48:59,337 --> 00:49:01,806
Do you remember that?

775
00:49:05,410 --> 00:49:06,411
Something I want?

776
00:49:07,378 --> 00:49:10,548
That would be a house.

777
00:49:13,918 --> 00:49:14,919
A house to go home to.

778
00:49:16,120 --> 00:49:19,924
Since you said that, I…

779
00:49:21,559 --> 00:49:23,127
became a realtor.

780
00:49:28,933 --> 00:49:33,438
And I changed my name to Kenji Rusudo.

781
00:49:37,875 --> 00:49:42,947
Manchichi, when did you realize
that I was Dojisuke?

782
00:49:45,049 --> 00:49:48,186
I found "Dojisuke"

783
00:49:49,120 --> 00:49:50,555
in the name "Kenji Rusudo".

784
00:49:54,525 --> 00:49:56,861
DOJISUKE

785
00:49:59,063 --> 00:50:02,133
Part of me wanted you
to realize who I really was.

786
00:50:04,669 --> 00:50:08,306
Did you already see
what you are standing next to?

787
00:50:12,210 --> 00:50:14,245
YOSHIO LOVES MANCHICHI

788
00:50:16,080 --> 00:50:17,749
My feelings have not changed since then.

789
00:50:20,318 --> 00:50:24,689
I still love you.

790
00:50:36,501 --> 00:50:38,302
Who cares about what others think?

791
00:50:38,369 --> 00:50:41,005
The husband is having an affair,
and the wife approved it.

792
00:50:41,072 --> 00:50:42,774
Are you okay with love
outside of marriage?

793
00:50:42,840 --> 00:50:45,009
-Good evening.
-Oh, it started!

794
00:50:45,076 --> 00:50:46,411
We have a suggestion.

795
00:50:46,477 --> 00:50:47,578
Home and Eros.

796
00:50:47,645 --> 00:50:50,615
We will carry out
the important mission to sell a home.
